caption: We got the trio with the brambleberry crumble, the coconut cold brew and the black forest. By far, my favorite was the black forest which seems to be a new arrival - it was dark chocolate icecream with chocolate fudge, chocolate chips, and chocolate flecks and it was just absolutely delicious. Also their little waffle pieces are great too.
Always the best call - Wildberry lavender 😋

Five stars aren’t enough! Due to covid there was only one group allowed in the building at one time, but the person working the counter was quick so the wait wasn’t long at all! They were so nice and helpful! I got one scoop of the brambleberry ice cream and it was to die for!! Definitely will be visiting again.

Have you ever discovered a new color that no human has ever had the pleasure of viewing before? Have you ever made a sound so unique, so pure and so blissful that babies with colic immediately stop crying? Me neither. Because those things are hard to do. But I’ll tell you what I did do today. I had some of Jeni’s Splendid Ice Cream. And let me tell you what, that is the closest I will ever come to discovering a new sense. I fell in love today. That love came in the form of Gooey Butter Cake. In the great words of Forest Gump aka Hank the Tank, I love you Jeni.
Hands down, favorite ice cream!
So delicious. They have great flavors, and a few dairy free options. Clean and efficient.
Always great experience. Definitely a place to visit and try new flavors.  Dairy free coconut coffee the best.
Turkish coffee ice cream is so good. It's a must try. Ice cream is thick and has the right strong coffee taste. I didn't really like the signature flavors though.
Filled me up in no time. I had a brother come into town and he asked me to go back here. The bill was fair I would say.
Love it

Terrible, my boyfriend and I purchased a pint of Banana Creme Pudding ice cream and it tasted like fake flavors and plastic. We spent $12 on a little container and we can't even return it. There is always a line but it is absolutely not worth it. Store bought is ten times better.  Really disgusted and unhappy!
saffron /wildberry lavender/ almond butter so good
Very distinctive flavors
Super place to meet and chat with coworkers. The service was very welcoming and observant. Prices were appropriate.
Excellent spot to spend time alone or talk business. The service was very welcoming and observant. This place has a cool atmosphere.
Honestly one of the best flavors and decent price!

I'd give them 5 stars if they had a vegan waffle cone option and a bit more variety of vegan flavors. However, we can't always have it all and Jeni's excels at what it does! The ice cream is always luxurious, airy, creamy and delicious with the perfect mouth feel--no easy feat for vegan ice cream! Plus, the parlor is always sparkling clean and the staff are just as sweet as the offerings!

The best ice cream ever.  The flavors are unique and we'll blended -- not too sweet or too salty.  It is worth every cent.  Unfortunately because of the COVID pandemic they are not offering samples so that you can find your favorite flavors.
Really good icecream, social distancing and masks required, no more than two people ordering! My chocolate truffle was really good!
Very good ice cream& service
First time trying and was simply delicious! Honey Vanilla Bean best ever 👍🏾

Socially distanced and great ice cream! Jeni's is a favorite of mine and a place I'll go again and again. This location is in the popular restaurant row in west loop. Service was prompt, friendly and quick!
Really good ice cream! I had the upside-down pineapple!

Columbus, Ohio originated ice cream powerhouse opens another Chicago location west of the loop in the Randolph / Fulton Market neighborhood. One can really not go wrong with any flavor choice. The brilliance, bouquet, and bursting ice cream flavors truly have no rival or equivalence. My typical go to options are Darkest Chocolate and the former Buckeye State. Yet, do not shy away from the fruit and floral creations which defy description.
Ice cream there is so great and tasty. I like they have upstairs area so you can enjoy your ice cream there. It’s pricey but it worth. Now is my favorite ice cream.

getting a double scoop with waffle cone was relatively well priced. they have interesting flavors that border on pretentious but just barely step back. which is to say - the ice cream flavors are imaginative and easy to enjoy.
Butter Cake is Tucker approved 👌🏼
Omg. Get the salted Carmel. Thank me later.
Love this ice cream, even though my favorite flavor wasn't out yet I still found another one that I equally enjoyed
Awesome
Always a good time for Jeni's.  Chicago's Best!
Great workers and quick turnaround.

Wow. Wow. Got 4 flavors to share (all with the fam, no worries), and each one was so distinct in nature from the others. Each one was completely unique in consistency, flavor, even aroma (I'm told they use essential oils in their wild berry lavender). It's clear they put a lot of thought, care, and creativity into each offering.
Great ice cream & love the smell and taste of a freshly made waffle cone! Almond butter brittle is my fave! Try the 3 scoop trio.

Even though there's always a line, it moves pretty quickly. Ice cream is excellent and they have an upstairs area for seating. If you can't walk up or down the stairs they do have an elevator only for the handicap. They also offer shipping
1 word.  Brambleberry.
This location has always had exceptional service.  The flavors are always wonderful and the fact it has upstairs seating is a wonder in this city.  So much room!
Best ice cream to me
Best ice cream in the city!
Good. It's definitely overrated. The line is super long. I'm vegan and they have multiple options, but I've definitely had better vegan ice cream.
Very good ice cream and the waffle cones were delicious. A little expensive though

Good quality ice cream with a wide set of amazing flavours. We tried 2 half scoops of buttery gooey ice cream which was amazing and the milkiest chocolate. I did not like the waffle cone much as it was too salty and too crispy. Overall its a great place for icecream with good ambience.
Great quality ice cream and plenty of seating
Hands down the best ice cream I've ever had.
Yes please. I would eat dessert here every day (after each meal) if it wouldn't take so many years off my life
Gourmet ice cream at its finest! Bit pricey but definitely worth it. Fresh ingredients and inventive flavors

I am in love with Jeni's Ice Creams and it hurts me to put this at 4 stars. The staff is amazing, the ice cream is high quality, but the major problem is the location. Parking is limited and there are a large number of restaurants and bars in the area, which makes for a large amount of traffic. However, it does not disappoint as a Jeni's and I would visit again when I have a craving for ice cream
I cried when it was gone.
I love ice cream, and I know what’s good- this is good
Best icecream in the world!!!

Ice cream is delicious. However, the lines are way too long. Please serve the people in line before the online orders.  Seems like the more popular this place becomes the smaller the scoops become. Please help the very expensive ice cream scoop seem worth it.
Trendy ice cream place.  Now with west loop location.  Gives you another dessert option after drinking
Quality ice cream in the West loop!
Nice place. Flavors you won't. See anyplace else. One scoop is $5.50. But try the half scoops to get the Jeni's experience.  3 half scoops for $6.50. Limited seating
Best ice cream in Chicago! Lovely place😻
Best ice cream i have ever had.
The boozy eggnog is to die for. Absolutely fabulous
All I can say is: get a double scoop of the gooey butter cake in a freshly made waffle cone.  😍😋
This is honestly the best ice cream I’ve ever had. It’s so rich. I recommend Cream Puff or Gooey Butter Cake. Beware, on a Friday or Saturday night the line is easily wrapping out the store.
Yummy

The smell of freshly made waffle bowls and cones drew me inside. Once inside, I sampled today's specials. The really helpful and friendly staff allowed me to decide which flavors to devour in my waffle bowl. Ample indoor seating allowed me to enjoy my tastey treat. Will definitely go back!
Best ice cream in Chicago!
Serves very unique flavours of ice cream in cozy setting tucked in a place near Morgan Station. If you happen not to be counting calories, definitely stop by.
Expect waiting in line

I went here for a post final exam celebration with some friends. The ice cream was fantastic, but the smells were even better! As soon as you open the front door, a rich and spicy aroma hits you (all from their waffles).
I love places with interesting flavors.
Nice ice creams. Great flavors.
I love places with interesting flavors.
Always good. Probably the BEST ice cream I've ever had. 2 best flavors are the Brambleberry and the Brown Butter Almond Brittle.

Dang good ice cream.  If you just want a good classic strawberry or vanilla... WELL THIS AIN'T THE PLACE!  This is like chef grade, after hours,  experimentation and all those hypothesis turn out great. I had goat cheese and cherry... that's right... and I loved it.
Super delicious icecream. Always long lines in the summer.  So good.

Terrible customer service! The ice-cream may be splendid but the customer service is slow and sluggish.  I was there around 4PM today, I patiently waited but the workers served customers before and after me, Both of them. He also helped customers who wanted to purchase pints before serving me. Customers behind me informed worker I am next but he/she ignored it, looked at me and continued serving others.  When I told the ice-cream server that I am next he told me I will be served with my group.  I told him I am not with a group and that I have been waiting but he continued arguing with me.  In addition,  the waffle maker dropped a waffle while making cones.  I will never walk in or purchase Jeni's ice-cream.
Line's too long
I tried the eggnog and gingerbread ice creams. The eggnog is great while the gingerbread needs a bit more ginger.
Who doesn't like Jenni's, seriously?

The line was long, but moved quickly. The workers were friendly and efficient. My friend even got a free scoop for her birthday! There were so many flavors that it was hard to choose just one, so I got three scoops, and they were all delicious.
Yummy. And, the Iine moved quickly.
Love, love, love this place. Amazing ice cream and great vibe!
Never disappoints
Delicious, even in the middle of winter!
Wow. Just wow. On par with Comfy Cow in Louisville.
Homemade waffle cones,  enough said.

Wow amazing how creative all the different ice creams are and the taste is Woooow too ;)

The ice cream was fantastic! My only complaint is that it took quite a while for us to pay. We were just holding our ice creams at the counter, while the rest of the employees were scooping ice cream. Nonetheless, will come back again!

If you don’t mind sharing I would recommend getting the three half scoops. This lest you have more flavors if you are an undeceive sugar addict like me.  We had the “Darkest Chocolate”, “Wildberry Lavender”, and something else...

Fun flavors, lots of cake and cookie flavors that are gluten free too!! 😍

(Translated by Google) High-quality ice cream shop that surpasses gelato. The price is $ 6 per scoop, but it's worth the price. It's like gelato, but it preserves the unique flavor of milk fat. The sweetness is gentle, not like the American dessert. Waffle cones also have crispness and softness and are sweet. You can try different flavors, so try as much as you can and decide. It's not a luxurious ice cream, but the basics are the perfect regular ice cream.  (Original) 젤라또를 능가하는 고급 아이스크림집. 한 스쿱에 6불이라은 가격을 자랑하지만 그 정도 값에 걸맞는 맛이다. 젤라또처럼 쫀득하지만 특유의 유지방 맛을 잘 보존하고 있다. 미국의 디저트답지 않게 단맛의 강함이 신사적이다. 와플콘도 바삭함과 부드러움을 같이 겸비하고 있으며 달짝지근하다. 다양한 맛을 먹어볼 수 있으니, 최대한 많이 시식해보고 결정하자. 고급스러운 아이스크림은 아니지만 기본기가 완벽한 일반 아이스크림이라고 할 수 있다.

(Translated by Google) Creamy ice cream in the Loop West, cafes, restaurants in a very pleasant atmosphere.  (Original) Helado cremoso en el Loop West,  cafés,  restaurantes en un ambiente muy agradable.
Lovely crew, loooong Q , the taste not worth their line time
Love it!!!
Creamy, very natural, homemade-tasting ice cream! Texas Sheet Cake and Salted Peanut Butter are the best!!! Small dining area, though, and the line can get pass the door.

There's a reason why the line is always out the doors--the ice cream here is just that good. Out of all the Jeni's locations in Chicago, this is probably my favorite because there is ample seating on the first and second story. Some other things that are great:  - Permanent signature flavors and rotating seasonal flavors keep bringing me back - Wildberry lavender and brown butter almond brittle are the best ice creams in the world - Scoopers are soo friendly and let you try as many samples as you want - Buttercrisp waffle cone is hands down the best ice cream cone you will ever have. Just get it. Pay for it. It's worth it.
Best ice cream in Chicago
the tip proposal by the cashier table is embarrassing
I honestly kinda want to dislike Jeni's because of the price, but i can't--their ice cream rocks, service at this location is great, and the environment is so welcoming and awesome for groups.

Truly Splendid Ice Cream!!! There is no denying that the execution is on point with intense creaminess, luscious ice crystal structure and flavor forward - what more can you ask for.  Each flavor we tired was absolutely on point and what is more exciting is the number of choices, many of which are incredible unique only lifting their status as ice cream supreme.  The price tag is high, but I have said it so many time - when the product is able to be delivered so flawlessly the price is justified and I wouldn't think twice about paying what I did for the ice cream. Ice Cream may be my guiltiest of pleasures and I consider myself deeply experienced in ice cream tasting (quite proud) - trust me this is the CREAM of the crop!!!
The best American style icecream in Chicago in my opinion. I visited her retail spot in Ohio many years ago before she expanded to other states.
This is some serious ice cream.
Unique and delicious.

Jeni's never lets me down...except when they run out of flavors, but I think this just shows how many people they have go in on a daily basis and how many people absolutely love the ice cream here. I have yet to run into a rude or impatient employee at any Jeni's location I've been to. I've actually been to this location a handful of times, but I just recently went upstairs! It's pretty and very roomy upstairs. In the women's restroom there are two stalls and they even have tampons in there! I absolutely love that they have a landfill bin, recycle, and compost. The bowls that the give you your ice cream in, along with the spoons are all compostable. Still trying to figure out what goes in the landfill bin, when this company is so green!  This time around, I tried the Atlantic Beach Pie. If you don't like sour flavors or any tartness whatsoever skip over it. The lemony tartness is so refreshing. When I read in the description that there was a teensy mix of saltine in it, I was skeptical. However, after a taste it wasn't too apparent and as a whole was tasty enough to convince me to get a whole scoop!

(Translated by Google) Excellent ice cream shop. Ice cream made with natural ingredients and several lactose free options.  (Original) Sorveteria excelente. Sorvetes feitos somente com ingredientes naturais e diversas opções sem lactose.
Excellent ice cream shop! The flavor are original and the ice cream tastes great!
Open late, so when everything else in the area was closed, and I needed to use the washroom, I could go there. Darkest Chocolate in a waffle cone.
Be ready for a long line, but be assured it is worth waiting to have this extremely delicious American-style ice cream! Ask for the waffle bowl or cone to have the full experience.
Delicious ice cream, very kind and patient. Really recommend this place

They have a lot of unique flavors, the honey and lavender were decent to me. The honeycake was incredibly salty to me unfortunately, it made me feel sick and I had to throw it out ): hopefully just a fluke.
There is something in the ice cream that makes it impossible to stop coming back.
Very nice. The darkest chocolate was super!

so hot outside ice cream melted quick

The LINE out the front door that Continues down the sidewalk is...TOTALLY WORTH IT! Signature flavor Gooey Butter Cake has my undivided attention. Seasonal flavor Nectar Honey actually tastes like Summer. AND their Buttercrisp waffle cone/bowl... Make that a regulatory requirement for eating ice cream. Oh, And the STAFF...straight Chilling. (Sorry, Couldn’t help it.) Repeat customer. Need I say more?
Great ice cream... They let you same anything and everything so that you can decide what ya truly want

As good ice cream should be.  I had vanilla it was the best I've had in a long, long time. Good service Had the right number of people helping the customers. And a separate person taking the money.  Great plan. Thank you from a visitor from  South Carolina!!
That's some good ice cream! Everyone was really nice and helpful, it was pretty inexpensive too. A must try, don't wait!

Love! It's everything you want an ice cream shop to be! The smell of waffles fills the air even before you enter. There is usually a line outside so they have an area marked off for the line. We waited in line too for about 10 minutes but the smell fills you up that you don't even mind waiting. The outside is very modern yet old school, Miami vibe yet Chicago, busy yet worth it. The inside is white with splashes of color with their decor choices such as books, t shirts, plants, etc. I really liked their details and their menu design - very simplistic and creative. The ice cream flavors caters to everyone and then some more. Everything and I mean everything tastes wonderful and true to their names. I tried a bunch of flavors before getting my order and I already am looking forward to try new ones in my next visit. They use metal spoons that are reusable for tasting which I appreciate instead of plastic spoons which is environmentally friendly. The staff working were very helpful, sweet and just the kind of people you expect to be working in an ice cream store. There were all age group of people getting their ice cream servings so when you have some time, you must visit!  Tip: if you are getting a pint because you already know the flavor you want, then just go to the cashier and get the pint from them directly. You can skip any line if buy the pint!
Good ice cream. Long lines.
Interesting flavors and delicious waffle cones. Their ice cream is thick and almost chewy
Make this a "Must" when in Chicago.
Clean, smells good, great service, free samples, amazing ice cream
Always love going to a Jeni's every chance I get. The flavors are so rich. The ice cream melts slowly and isn't stick like your beloved store bought I've cream. Definitely worth it.
Long lines... Tasty ice cream. Some people actually try 5 or more flavors, making everyone wait to order. Stop these people, Jenni! Put a limit on flavor samples!!!
Holy Sh!t this ice cream is not messing around. The best non-dairy ice cream I've had. Get the just-made waffle cone
Very good ice cream

Awesome! Awesome! Awesome! This is the best ice cream in Chicago...They have wonderful and flavors...many are unique and all of them delicous...I highly recommend Jeni's
Great ice cream, but the line moves too slowly. Flavors are really incredible though.
Good good good
The ice cream is very good! I had a non-dairy ice cream and you couldn't tell the difference! I will definitely be back and if you are in the area it is definitely worth the stop!
Some of the best ice cream I've ever had!!!

Non-Dairy in the house!!! Yes! Their Texas Sheet Cake non dairy is insane. Got a drop of it on my finger and almost ate my hand.

Visited Chicago and was told we had to eat here. Walked past it after two different dinners on two different evenings and both times the lines looked like the wait would almost an hour. So we didn't stop. On our last full day in town we showed up at 11:00 in the morning and ate ice cream for lunch. It was SO GOOD!!! Totally worth making a special trip over there. Wish we had this in our neighborhood (though that would probably be dangerous). We all tried different flavors and everyone loved what they had. Totally worth the price. Will be back next time we're in Chicago!
It was good ice cream. I had the peanut butter w chocolate flakes and coffee brew coconut cream. But i didn't get the charge difference if u sat in to eat it or leave ?? First time . It was cute
Other them the biiiiig line of people going in it’s an amazing Ice-cream! My partner and I love it!!!!

Great ice cream and allergy friendly!
Great ice cream! There's always a line due to its trendiness at tube moment. There could be more scoopers to combat this.
Honestly, if I could marry Jeni's, I would. Jeni's make me incredibly happy. I love you Jeni's. 👰🏻🍨💍💒
Staff is great! Super cute location too. If you’re in the area and driving, be aware of a lack of parking. We spent 20 minutes trying to find a spot
nice place with good service, and creative, delicious ice cream flavors.

Nice find in Chicago. More choices than a reasonable person could process. I had sun-popped corn ice cream. Delicious!
Great ice cream. I had dark chocolate one and it was delicious. The cones are made on the premises and the smell is overwhelming.

The long line was expected as the ice cream is top notch.  Definitely worth the 15 minute wait. The staff was friendly and well informed.  Would definitely come again.  Thos was our first time here. The flavors we got was delicious.
Ice cream was delicious. They have different flavors and sizes.
As good as any other Jeni's location.  Some of the best/most creative ice cream you can get in the city.
Icecream starts off well. Very light and mild in flavor, but quickly just starts tasting like butter. Cones are very salty and wrecks the taste. It's an okay icecream cone.
Freshly made waffle cones with a great selection of creamy ice creams.

Line was out the door and I considered leaving but I stayed and do not regret it. Had the amazing double chocolate and cake waffle cone. Joe was amazingly patient and talked me through the flavor options. They showed grace and made the experience wonderful. Highly recommend a must go if you are in the area. Only complaint is it is not cheap but if it was how long would the line be...
Made me love ice cream again.
Best ice cream ever... and it should be as it is quite pricey for ice cream, but their flavors are out of this world and the servings are generous. If you’re visiting the city, definitely try it.

It smells so delightful when you walk past let alone when you actually go in. The staff are so friendly and sweet. You can watch them make their fresh butter crisp waffle cone. I got chocolate cone and it had fresh brownies and everything! They even have a small cone for kids! Family friendly and definitely I recommend. Their ice cream taste is like no other I have ever tasted!
Mmm, mmm good!
Friendly, colorful, and most importantly - tasty
Delicious ice cream! My favorite is the Darkest Chocolate, but you can't go wrong with anything.

My favorite ice cream place in Chicago! Many creative flavors and they all are very tasty! Also have non-dairy options (cold brew with coconut cream is my favorite). I’ve been going to Jeni’s at least once a week since their west loop location has opened.
So many amazing and diverse flavors,  there is something for everyone.

There is always a line coming out of Jeni’s and you should expect to wait 15-30 minutes. Part of it is because most people will try samples which slows down the turn around.  Ice cream: 4 stars Selection: 5 stars Service: 4.25 stars Overall: 4.25 stars Recommendations: get the waffle cone, single is more than enough for one person  The ice cream here is definitely better than your mass market chain ( Baskin-Robbins, Hagen dazz, etc). But it’s not amazing and you probably will have had better if you at an ice cream fan. The real cool thing about this place is the unique flavors that they have, which you are unlikely to find anywhere else. The waffle cone here is very good and is a stand out among waffle cones.
Excellent choices of ice cream served in waffle bowl/cone. Delicious.
Great selection. Different flavors like peach and biscuit or pb and j. Always experimenting
I love their unique ice creams.
Yummies galore.
Amazing ice cream. The best in the city. Great dairy free options.

So many flavors. they hand role their sugar cones. Flavor menu is always changing. This is a great place for dessert after a night out in west loop. Note that line ups get longer around after dinner hours!! But totally worth it.
Very smooth, accurate descriptions of flavors, many flavors are more savory than sweet.
So happy its now in the west loop!!! Gooey butter cake all the way!

I was searching online for a dessert place and was curious when I read that Jeni's has unique flavors. The line was to the door which was fine. It gave me a chance to read all the different signs in the store.  Since I had this one chance, I wasn't quite sure how I was going to narrow down my choice to one flavor. Thankful for the Trio which is 3 half scoops! I got the Strawberry Buttermilk, Wildberry Lavender and Cold Brew with Coconut Cream and a taste of the waffle crisp. The half scoops are pretty generous.  Behind the register area, they had pint size ice cream for folks who need to bring some home.  I had gone to the seating area upstairs to slowly enjoy every bite.  Surely found a sweet gem!
Good ice cream

This place is a must go when you visit Chicago. I take all my friends from out of town to try the ice cream here, I have yet to find another ice cream shop that is as good as Jeni’s. We went to the grand opening. The line was super long. That's a testament to how good this place is. They have great company stories and they care about putting the best ice creams together for their customers. Give yourself some time to read through their menu and know what flavors you want. 100 as always 💕💕💕
Jeni's is awesome! I've been to several locations and they never disappoint. My favorites are the frosé, darkest chocolate, and wildberry lavender.

Jeni’s is my favorite ice cream place in the city. They also have frozen yogurt and a good amount of non-dairy options.  Great place to stop for a date and make googley eye at each other or to pick up a pint to go on the way to a dinner party. This ice cream is fancy enough to serve on its own.  I recommend the Goat Cheese and Red Cherries.
